"Noppel F., Singh R.","Overview on contrail and cirrus cloud avoidance technology",2007,"Journal of Aircraft","44","5",,"1721","1726",,,10.2514/1.28655,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-36348993865&partnerID=40&md5=f0cf863f18124770d08b4687c0504cbe","Cranfield University, Bedfordshire, MK43 0AL, United Kingdom; School of Engineering, Department of Power and Propulsion, United Kingdom","Noppel, F., Cranfield University, Bedfordshire, MK43 0AL, United Kingdom, School of Engineering, Department of Power and Propulsion, United Kingdom; Singh, R., Cranfield University, Bedfordshire, MK43 0AL, United Kingdom, School of Engineering, Department of Power and Propulsion, United Kingdom","Greenhouse gas emissions, contrails, and aviation-induced cirrus clouds are the principal pollutants from air traffic, which contribute to the anthropogenic global warming. Recent climate assessments have stressed the importance of contrails and aviation-induced cirrus clouds because they may contribute more than all other aircraft emissions combined. This paper reviews the mechanisms of contrail and aviation-induced cirrus cloud formation from which avoidance strategies are derived and discussed. Copyright © 2007 by the Cranfield University. Published by the American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics, Inc.",,"Anthropogenic global warming; Cirrus clouds; Cloud avoidance; Air transportation; Collision avoidance; Gas emissions; Global warming; Greenhouse gases; Clouds",,,,,,"Hansen, J., Sato, M., Ruedy, R., Radiative Forcing Climate Response (1997) Journal of Geophysical Research, 102 (D6), pp. 6831-6864. , March; Aviation and the Global Atmosphere (1999) A Special Report of IPCC Working Groups, pp. I-III. , Penner, J. E, Lister, D. H, Griggs, D. J, Dokken, D. J, and McFarland, M, eds, and, Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, U.K; Sausen, R., Isaksen, I., Grewe, V., Hauglustaine, D., Lee, D., Gunnar, M., Köhler, M.P., Zerefos, C., Aviation Radiative Forcing in 2000: 